    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fortified enclosures constructed on a raised block of land that forms a promontory of some kind projecting out from a hillside or cliff line. The main defenses cut off the neck of the promontory, the remainder of the perimeter having natural defensive capabilities. Most date back to the Iron Age.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
